Cronobacter sakazakii sequence types 1, 4, 8 and 12 are associated with outbreaks of
neonatal meningitis and necrotizing enterocolitis infections. However clonality results in
strains which are indistinguishable using conventional methods. This study investigated the
use of clustered regularly interspaced short palindromic repeats (CRISPR)¨Ccas loci profling
for epidemiological investigations